		</div>
	</div>
</div>While I've found Linux is generally quite good at this, Windows 8/7 have been generally fine when I've had to install them. Often all I needed to install was the sound card driver and GPU driver, which I just downloaded the driver for... and install.<br />
<br />
OC XP is hell to install now days, as it has so little support for any new hardware, but then again its 11 years old (7 for later releases) I doubt a 7 years old Linux installer would work nicely out of the box either.
